1. Figure out the exact organization name from the IMAP/POP3 service and submit it as the answer.

nmap <ADDRESS> -p 110,143, 993,995 -sV -sC 
the name of the company shows here in the SSL cert.

2. What is the FQDN that the IMAP and POP3 servers are assigned to?
 
as above, the FQDN is also in the SSL cert.

3. Enumerate the IMAP service and submit the flag as the answer. (Format: HTB{...})

openssl s_client -connect <ADDDRESS>:imaps

There is a read block at the bottom containing the flag

4. What is the customized version of the POP3 server?

openssl s_client -connect <ADDDRESS>:pop3s

Again, the version is in the read block here as above, the answer is fullname InFreight... vx.xxx 

5. What is the admin email address?

For these we need to look up FETCH options in detail 

connect with opensll, USER robin (from previous exercise on smtp) -OK password same as username...

1 LOGIN username password (1 is the command tag) 
1 LIST "" * - lists all directories, the inbox is DEV.DEPARTMENT.INT
1 SELECT DEV.DEPARTMENT.INT - this shows "1 exists" that there is one email
1 FETCH 1 BODY[HEADER] - returns the headers including To: and From: - containing the email address.

The admin username is here

6. Try to access the emails on the IMAP server and submit the flag as the answer. (Format: HTB{...})

login to the imap server using ssl as above, 
repeat the steps from 5 and then 
`1 FETCH 1 BODY[TEXT]

The message body data itself contains the htb{xxx} code 
